As investors continue to reposition ahead of the third-quarter earnings, the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) extended its winning streak to three successive sessions, causing the All Share Index (ASI) to increase further by 0.28 per cent.
 
At the close of transactions yesterday, the ASI appreciated by 80.90 absolute points or 0.28 per cent to close at 28,777.96 points. Similarly, the market capitalisation gained N43 billion to close at N15.042 trillion.  Also, analysts at Afrinvest Limited expect the performance of the equities market to be dictated by the earnings results.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .